{"id":14880798,"mediaExerciseId":"3f9c96b0-1ebb-4eff-abae-3c265843bc1d","exerciseName":"3","chapterName":"3","chapterTitle":"Working with Financial Statements","groupId":612275,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":85,"solutions":[{"id":5949805,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we are required to determine the receivables turnover, days’ sales in receivables and how long it took, on average, for credit customers to pay off their accounts during the past year.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Before we proceed with the first requirement, let us first define receivables turnover.\n\n**Receivables turnover** is used to measure the effectiveness of a company in extending credit as well as collecting debts.\n\nThe formula is denoted as follows:\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\textbf{Receivables turnover}& =\n \\dfrac{\\text{Net Credit Sales}} {\\text{Average Accounts Receivable}}\\\\ \\\\\n\\end{aligned}$$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"To determine the receivables turnover:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\textbf{Receivables turnover}& =\n \\dfrac{\\text{Net Credit Sales}} {\\text{Average Accounts Receivable}}\\\\ \\\\\n& = \\frac{\\$5,473,640} {\\$537,810}\\\\ \\\\\n&= \\boxed{10.18}\\\\\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nIn conclusion, the receivables turnover for Twist Corp. is 10.18.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"Before we proceed with the second requirement, let us first define days’ sales in receivables.\n\n**Days’ sales in receivables** shows the number of days it takes to collect the company's accounts receivable.\n\nThe formula is denoted as follows:\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\textbf{Days’ sales in receivables}& =\n \\dfrac{\\text{Accounts Receivable}} {\\text{Net Credit Sales}} \\times {\\text{365 days}}\\\\ \\\\\n\\end{aligned}$$\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":103,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/27/92ce723c5c9f5e4204971e712cbd0bd7/7f551eed4533cec669d1920b3eef98cf/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/27/92ce723c5c9f5e4204971e712cbd0bd7/7f551eed4533cec669d1920b3eef98cf/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"To determine the Days’ sales in receivables:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\textbf{Days’ sales in receivables}& =\n \\dfrac{\\text{Accounts Receivable}} {\\text{Net Credit Sales}} \\times {\\text{365 days}}\\\\ \\\\\n& = \\frac{\\$537,810} {\\$5,473,640}  \\times {\\text{365}}\\\\ \\\\\n&= \\boxed{35.86}\\\\\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nIn conclusion, the days’ sales in receivables for Twist Corp. is 35.86.\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":358,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/27/92ce723c5c9f5e4204971e712cbd0bd7/4c9b6470733f0f744b3e071a9ac96e25/lateximg_large.png","width":871},"regular":{"height":181,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/27/92ce723c5c9f5e4204971e712cbd0bd7/4c9b6470733f0f744b3e071a9ac96e25/lateximg.png","width":435}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"On average, it takes 35.86 days for credit customers to pay off their accounts during the past year.\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":28,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/27/92ce723c5c9f5e4204971e712cbd0bd7/c52056e1ccef093415dfeec25420d0a6/lateximg_large.png","width":843},"regular":{"height":15,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/27/92ce723c5c9f5e4204971e712cbd0bd7/c52056e1ccef09341